e%20right%20thing%20is%20almost%20always%20an%20exercise%20in%20empathy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERaising%20kids%20without%20entitlement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20a%20question%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fteach-kids-appreciate-wealth-privilege-2022-1%5C%22%3Ea%20parent%20trying%20not%20to%20spoil%20their%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20their%20kids%20had%20a%20lot%20more%20financial%20privilege%20than%20the%20parent%20had%20growing%20up.%20It%20wasn't%20a%20stretch%20to%20empathize%20with%20this%20person%3B%20my%20story%20is%20quite%20similar.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20financially%20better%20off%20than%20my%20parents%20were%2C%20and%20because%20of%20this%2C%20my%20kids%20have%20more%20than%20I%20ever%20did%20at%20their%20ages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20firsthand%20that%20the%20parent%20was%20likely%20experiencing%20two%20feelings%3A%20a%20genuine%20concern%20that%20too%20much%20privilege%20can%20lead%20to%20spoiled%20children%20and%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20personal%20envy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20nothing%20that%20forces%20us%20to%20face%20our%20childhood%20wounds%20quite%20like%20raising%20children.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20we%20are%20in%20our%20parents'%20shoes%2C%20understanding%20the%20pressures%20that%20led%20them%20to%20make%20the%20decisions%20that%20would%20define%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20this%2C%20I%20encouraged%20my%20reader%20to%20do%20something%20I%20strive%20to%20do%20with%20my%20children%3A%20Allow%20their%20childhood%20experience%20to%20inform%20how%20they%20raise%20their%20children%20without%20letting%20their%20scars%20interfere%20with%20that%20relationship.%20On%20a%20more%20concrete%20level%2C%20I%20also%20advised%20the%20reader%20to%20teach%20their%20kids%20gratitude%20at%20every%20turn%2C%20especially%20through%20the%20example%20they%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWorrying%20about%20kids'%20financial%20choices%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20all%20of%20the%20parents%20who%20are%20writing%20me%20are%20still%20raising%20their%20kids%20like%20I%20am.%20This%20is%20why%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20parent%20worried%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fson-wont-stop-wasting-money-mind-own-business-2023-12%5C%22%3Etheir%20son's%20purchase%20of%20a%20%2470%2C000%20pickup%20truck%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20drew%20my%20advice%20from%20my%20experience%20as%20a%20mother%20and%20as%20a%20daughter.%20I%20am%20all%20too%20familiar%20with%20how%20it%20feels%20to%20have%20parents%20lecturing%20me%20on%20my%20choices%20as%20a%2030-plus-year-old%20woman.%20It's%20always%20annoying%2C%20especially%20when%20they're%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20adult%20daughter%2C%20my%20advice%20was%20obvious%20%E2%80%94%20parents%20need%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20their%20adult%20children's%20financial%20affairs%20%E2%80%94%20but%2C%20as%20a%20mother%2C%20I%20know%20just%20how%20difficult%20that%20can%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20like%20to%20think%20that%20I%20will%20quit%20feeling%20so%20deeply%20invested%20in%20my%20children's%20experience%20of%20the%20world%20as%20they%20get%20older%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20likely.%20So%20I%20tempered%20my%20advice%20with%20this%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGiving%20money%20to%20kids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20reader%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fgave-son-money-no-strings-attached-husband-wants-pay-2023-12%5C%22%3Egave%20their%20son%20%2416%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20now%20feels%20pressured%20by%20their%20spouse%20to%20seek%20repayment%2C%20I%20had%20no%20experiences%20to%20compare%20it%20to.%20However%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20know%20how%20it%20feels%20to%20be%20caught%20between%20loved%20ones%2C%20pressured%20on%20both%20sides%20to%20appease%20one%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20this%20happens%2C%20there%20never%20feels%20like%20a%20correct%20answer.%20So%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20the%20feelings%20out%20of%20it%20for%20the%20reader's%20sake%20and%20focus%20solely%20on%20the%20facts.%20This%20meant%20focusing%20on%20the%20original%20agreement.%20Was%20it%20a%20gift%20or%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-personal-loans%5C%22%3Eloan%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20By%20sticking%20to%20the%20original%20agreement%2C%20no%20one%20could%20blame%20the%20reader%20for%20following%20through%20on%20their%20commitment%20and%20expecting%20everyone%20else%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20despite%20this%20being%20the%20practical%20solution%2C%20I%20recognized%20that%20the%20reader%20wouldn't%20have%20the%20luxury%20of%20removing%20their%20feelings%20from%20the%20situation%20and%20focusing%20only%20on%20the%20facts%2C%20so%20I%20wanted%20to%20let%20them%20know%20their%20feelings%20were%20valid.%20The%20pressure%20they%20felt%20to%20pick%20a%20side%20was%20unfair%20and%20not%20their%20fault.%20I%20also%20try%20to%20remember%20that%20good%20advice%20only%20goes%20so%20far%3B%20sometimes%2C%20you%20just%20need%20someone%20to%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENo%20matter%20what%2C%20I%20try%20to%20start%20with%20empathy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20week%2C%20I%20receive%20several%20messages%20from%20readers%20telling%20me%20they%20love%20or%20hate%20my%20advice.%20Recently%2C%20I%20received%20two%20messages%20on%20the%20same%20day%20in%20response%20to%20the%20same%20article.%20One%20reader%20began%20their%20letter%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20advice%20is%20going%20to%20hurt%20more%20than%20it%20helps.%26quot%3B%20The%20other%20reader%20felt%20differently%2C%20writing%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20were%20clearly%20born%20to%20do%20this%20work.%20Your%20advice%20is%20astounding.%26quot%3B%20(I%20may%20have%20printed%20that%20one%20off%20to%20hang%20on%20my%20bedroom%20mirror%20as%20a%20daily%20affirmation.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20be%20writing%20an%20advice%20column%20if%20I%20thought%20my%20insight%20hurt%20more%20than%20it%20helped%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bastounding%26quot%3B%20may%20be%20a%20bit%20of%20an%20overstatement%20in%20the%20other%20direction.%20But%20I%20believe%2C%20to%20the%20core%20of%20who%20I%20am%2C%20that%20if%20we%20lead%20with%20empathy%2C%20wisdom%20is%20never%20far%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-find-financial-advisor%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELooking%20for%20advice%20on%20how%20your%20savings%2C%20debt%2C%20or%20another%20financial%20challenge%20is%20affecting%20your%20relationships%3F%20Write%20to%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%20using%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ethis%20Google%20form%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20