ts%20place%20and%20would%20unintentionally%20open%20that%20about%2015%20times%20a%20day%2C%20my%20brain%20subconsciously%20thinking%20it%20could%20reach%20Instagram.%20I%20had%20to%20do%20this%20with%20each%2C%20replacing%20every%20social%20media%20app%20with%20one%20that%20would%20at%20least%20give%20me%20something%20worthwhile%20to%20read%20or%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-x-rebrand-logo-memes-jokes-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EX%20was%20the%20hardest%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20nut%20to%20crack%2C%20and%20I%20underestimated%20how%20difficult%20it%20would%20be.%20When%20I%20look%20back%20now%2C%20I%20don't%20even%20really%20understand%20what%20I%20was%20doing%20on%20there.%20Was%20I%20worried%20I%20would%20miss%20a%20key%20piece%20of%20news%3F%20The%20latest%20topical%20joke%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20more%20time%20to%20do%20other%20things%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20I've%20missed%20anything%20now%20that%20I've%20gotten%20over%20it.%20But%20the%20FOMO%20was%2C%20without%20doubt%2C%20the%20worst%20part%20about%20quitting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGrowing%20up%20as%20Gen%20Z%20in%20the%20era%20of%20social%20media%20has%20made%20leaving%20it%20behind%20tough.%20All%20my%20friends%20still%20use%20it%2C%20as%20does%20nearly%20everyone%20else%20I%20speak%20to.%20When%20I%20tell%20them%20I%20quit%2C%20I%20usually%20receive%20a%20raised%20eyebrow%20followed%20by%20a%20%26quot%3BReally%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20been%20like%20overcoming%20an%20addiction.%20Though%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fhow-to-break-social-media-addiction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esocial%20media%20addictions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20aren't%20considered%20the%20same%20as%20serious%20addictions%20such%20as%20drugs%20or%20alcohol%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.addictioncenter.com%2Fdrugs%2Fsocial-media-addiction%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520a%2520new%2520study%2Cpathways%2520affect%2520decisions%2520and%2520sensations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethey%20change%20the%20balance%20of%20chemicals%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20your%20brain%20in%20the%20same%20way.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20actually%20experienced%20relapses%2C%20which%20might%20seem%20surprising.%20But%20I%20would%2C%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20re-download%20one%20of%20the%20apps.%20Or%20log%20on%20my%20laptop.%20It%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20cut%20it%20out%20altogether%2C%20and%20often%2C%20I'd%20have%20to%20use%20special%20apps%20that%20locked%20me%20out%20of%20my%20phone%20or%20blocked%20software%20on%20my%20laptop.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20seemed%20ridiculous%20that%20quitting%20these%20apps%20was%20such%20hard%20work.%20But%20having%20gone%20through%20it%2C%20it's%20been%20absolutely%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20change%20in%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fhow-to-calm-anxiety%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eanxiety%20levels%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20been%20particularly%20noticeable.%20I'm%20not%20suggesting%20it's%20a%20cure%20for%20anxiety%2C%20but%20I%20now%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20know%20everything%20that%20everyone%20is%20doing%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstagram%20and%20Facebook%2C%20where%20people%20post%20constantly%20about%20the%20most%20interesting%20part%20of%20their%20lives%2C%20had%20exacerbated%20this.%20The%20constant%20comparisons%20to%20others%20on%20these%20platforms%20caused%20part%20of%20the%20anxiety%2C%20leaving%20me%20feeling%20inadequate.%20I've%20been%20a