0of%20Japan%20for%20exercise%20Team%20Spirit%2084-1%20when%20the%20accidental%20collision%20occurred.%20This%20was%20just%20one%20of%20the%20military%20exercises%20in%20the%20series%20called%20Team%20Spirit%20that%20the%20US%20had%20participated%20in%20with%20South%20Korea%20over%20the%20course%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalsecurity.org%2Fmilitary%2Fops%2Fteam-spirit.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E19%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22594%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Korean%20Navy%20tank%20landing%20ship%20approaches%20the%20beach%20during%20exercise%20Team%20Spirit%20'82.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f8a0444af076d3cf917577%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Korean%20Navy%20tank%20landing%20ship%20approaches%20the%20beach%20during%20exercise%20Team%20Spirit%20'82.%3Cp%3EHUM%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20Soviet%20subs%20would%20often%20follow%20US%20vessels%20closely%20to%20gather%20intelligence%2C%20and%20USSR%20submarine%20K-314%20had%20been%20following%20the%20carrier%20for%20several%20days%20prior%20to%20the%20collision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20military%20officials%20were%20puzzled%20as%20to%20how%20the%20Victor%20I-class%20submarine%20didn't%20see%20the%20carrier%20before%20running%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BQuite%20honestly%2C%20I%20have%20to%20question%20the%20seamanship%20of%20the%20Soviet%20captain%20involved%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Navy%20officer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fpolitics%2F1984%2F03%2F22%2Fsoviet-sub-bumps-into-us-carrier%2F3c75515e-d492-4f6a-8f01-a023b6bc4c9c%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20Washington%20Post%20after%20the%20collision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20maritime%20accident%20occurred%2C%20submarine%20K-314%2C%20which