0areas%20in%20Bengaluru%20face%20a%20water%20crisis%20due%20to%20drying%20borewells.%20Media%20reports%20identify%20257%20locations%20at%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fkarnataka%2Fbengalurus-water-board-scrambles-for-solutions-as-city-stares-at-water-crisis%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erisk%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Responding%20to%20this%2C%20the%20Bangalore%20Water%20Supply%20and%20Sewerage%20Board%20(BWSSB)%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1SKqhhyNAcJxP29sBBuIBxpNssixPqjPe%2Fview%3Fusp%3Dsharing%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eissued%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0an%20order%20on%20March%208%2C%20prohibiting%20the%20use%20of%20drinking%20water%20for%20washing%20vehicles%2C%20gardening%2C%20and%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EVarious%20factors%20have%20contributed%20to%20this%20crisis%20in%20the%20city.%20The%20Urban%20Water%20Balance%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwelllabs.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FWELL-Labs_Bengaluru-Urban-Water-Balance-Report.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EReport%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20Bengaluru%2C%20released%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwelllabs.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWELL%20Labs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20city-based%20research%20organisation%2C%20highlights%20some%20of%20these%20concerns.%20Key%20aspects%20include%20reliance%20on%20over-exploited%20groundwater%2C%20limited%20access%20to%20BWSSB%20pipelines%2C%20neglected%20lake%20maintenance%2C%20and%20underutilisation%20of%20water%20treatment%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20factors%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkarnataka%2Fbengaluru%2Fbengaluru-water-crisis-scarcity-worsens-tanker-prices-surge-up-to-rs-2850-2913143%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresulted%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20in%20citizens%20and%20housing%20societies%20spending%20inordinate%20amounts%20on%20water%20tankers%E2%80%93a%2012%2C000-litre%20private%20tanker%20of%20water%20now%20costs%20Rs%202%2C850%20and%20more%20in%20areas%20that%20do%20not%20have%20piped%20Cauvery%20water%20connections%20and%20are%20affected%20by%20severe%20water%20shortage.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3ECity%E2%80%99s%20water%20pipeline%20mainly%20serves%20central%20zones%2C%20outskirts%20rely%20on%20groundwater%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20data%20compiled%20by%20WELL%20Labs%2C%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20demand%20for%20freshwater%20stands%20at%20approximately%202%2C632%20million%20litres%20per%20day%20(MLD).%20In%20addition%20to%20the%201%2C460%20MLD%20of%20Cauvery%20water%20supplied%20by%20the%20BWSSB%2C%20the%20city%20presently%20utilises%20an%20estimated%201%2C372%20MLD%20of%20groundwater%2C%20which%20is%20almost%20half%20of%20its%20water%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20calculates%20domestic%20demand%20based%20on%20a%20projected%20population%20of%2012.6%20million%20and%20an%20average%20per%20capita%20consumption%20of%20150%20litres%20per%20day.%20The%20total%20domestic%20demand%20alone%20adds%20up%20to%201%2C890%20MLD%2C%20exceeding%20the%20provision%20from%20the%20Cauvery%20piped%20water%20connection.%20This%20compels%20the%20expanding%20population%20in%20the%20outer%20periphery%20of%20the%20city%20to%20rely%20on%20tankers%20and%20private%20borewells%20for%20groundwater%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20draggable%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20contenteditable%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20data-height-original%3D%5C%22964%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fe.infogram.com%2F77cd76ef-190e-4a2c-ad86-ad0482560098%3Fsrc%3Dembed%5C%22%20data-mce-fragment%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Ground%20Water%20Availability%20%26amp%3B%20Extraction%20In%20Bangalore%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22964%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20BWSSB%E2%80%99s%20public%20water%20supply%20is%20primarily%20concentrated%20in%20the%20central%20areas%20of%20the%20city%2C%20where%20the%20population%20is%20lower%20compared%20to%20the%20rapidly%20growing%20suburbs.%20The%201%2C460%20MLD%20is%20exclusively%20available%20to%20core%20and%20urban-local-body%20areas%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report.%20In%20areas%20lacking%20public%20infrastructure%2C%20consumers%E2%80%93including%20a%20majority%20of%20commercial%20entities%E2%80%93resort%20to%20groundwater%20extracted%20from%20private%20borewells%2C%20tankers%2C%20and%20open%20wells.%20The%20number%20of%20private%20borewells%20in%20Bengaluru%20at%20present%20is%20difficult%20to%20estimate%20because%20of%20the%20failure%20of%20regulatory%20control%20on%20borewell%20drilling.%20A%20Right-to-Information%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fcitizenkamran%2Fstatus%2F1762827208555638993%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresponse%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0said%20there%20are%20108%20borewells%20in%20the%20city%E2%80%93but%20it%20does%20not%20account%20for%20the%20thousands%20of%20private%20borewells%20that%20have%20been%20dug%20by%20housing%20complexes%20and%20private%20residences%2C%20as%20also%20tech%20parks%20and%20other%20workspaces%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20technically%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20situation%20is%20alarming%20as%20groundwater%20recharge%20rates%20significantly%20lag%20extraction%20rates.%20According%20to%20Central%20Groundwater%20Authority%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcgwa-noc.gov.in%2FLandingPage%2FLatestUpdate%2FNCDGWR2023.pdf%23page%3D354%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edata%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%202023%2C%20all%20six%20assessment%20units%E2%80%93Bangalore%20City%2C%20Anekal%2C%20Yelahanka%2C%20Bangalore-East%2C%20Bangalore-North%20and%20Bangalore-South%E2%80%93in%20urban%20Bengaluru%20are%20overexploited.%20Natural%20groundwater%20recharge%20through%20green%20spaces%20and%20water%20bodies%20is%20as%20low%20as%20148%20MLD%E2%80%93one-tenth%20of%20the%20daily%20consumption.%20Rapid%20urbanisation%20is%20diminishing%20the%20remaining%20green%20spaces%20in%20the%20city%2C%20which%20is%20essential%20for%20aquifer%20recharge.%20The%20city%E2%80%99s%20green%20cover%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwgbis.ces.iisc.ac.in%2Fsdss%2FBUiS%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eshrunk%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%2028%25%20in%202010%20to%202.9%25%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20light%20of%20the%20crisis%2C%20the%20Bruhat%20Bengaluru%20Mahanagara%20Palike%20(BBMP)%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkarnataka%2Fbengaluru%2Fbbmp-s-water-shortage-plan-revitalise-borewells-dig-new-ones-boost-tanker-supply-2909082%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eearmarked%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Rs%20131%20crore%20for%20digging%20new%20borewells%20in%20affected%20regions.%20However%2C%20this%20initiative%20may%20prove%20ineffective%20due%20to%20the%20already%20depleted%20groundwater%20levels%20and%20inadequate%20mapping%20of%20these%20levels.%20In%20both%20the%20short-%20and%20long-term%2C%20such%20a%20measure%20could%20falter.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20would%20be%20more%20prudent%20to%20source%20water%20from%20unaffected%20areas%20in%20central%20Bengaluru%20and%20distribute%20from%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20remarked%20Shashank%20Palur%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20WELL%20Labs%20and%20a%20co-author%20of%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3ENeglected%20city%20lakes%20unable%20to%20retain%20rainfall%20runoff%20effectively%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGroundwater%20experts%20at%20WELL%20Labs%20emphasise%20the%20impact%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkarnataka%2Fkarnataka-records-34-northeast-monsoon-deficiency%2Farticle67544415.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einsufficient%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0rainfall%20in%20Karnataka%20in%202023.%20About%2045%25%20of%20this%20rainwater%20becomes%20runoff%2C%20entering%20rivers%20and%20lakes.%20However%2C%20these%20lakes%2C%20filled%20with%20treated%20and%20untreated%20wastewater%2C%20lack%20the%20capacity%20for%20rainwater%20storage%20or%20flood%20buffering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWithin%20the%20BBMP%2C%20173%20lakes%20span%20three%20valleys%20in%20cascading%20chains.%20This%20lake%20network%20is%20pivotal%20for%20urban%20flood%20management%2C%20designed%20to%20handle%20surpluses%20by%20allowing%20water%20to%20cascade%20from%20one%20lake%20to%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EInitially%2C%20these%20seasonal%20lakes%20filled%20entirely%20during%20monsoons%2C%20acting%20as%20flood%20buffers%20in%20periods%20of%20heavy%20rainfall.%20Urbanisation%20altered%20the%20inflow%20composition%3B%20roughly%20half%20the%20water%20entering%20lakes%20is%20wastewater%2C%20both%20treated%20and%20untreated.%20Consequently%2C%20most%20city%20lakes%20consistently%20remain%20full%2C%20leaving%20little%20room%20for%20monsoon%20rain.%20This%20is%20also%20responsible%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2Fbangalore%2Fbengaluru-most-vulnerable-to-urban-flooding-imd-data%2Farticle67878838.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eurban%20flooding%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0during%20the%20monsoon.%20Average%20runoff%20during%20monsoons%20(June%20to%20December)%20is%20around%20982%20MLD%E2%80%9373%25%20more%20than%20dry%20season%20runoff%20(568%20MLD)%2C%20states%20the%20report.%20Additionally%2C%20rampant%20construction%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20channels%20between%20lakes%20getting%20severed%2C%20with%20the%20result%20that%20overflows%20don%E2%80%99t%20flow%20to%20other%20lakes%20but%2C%20instead%2C%20cause%20urban%20flooding%20and%20water%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20draggable%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20contenteditable%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20data-height-original%3D%5C%22659%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fe.infogram.com%2Fb435b7bd-47d0-4efc-a6c7-3b99b8910ab9%3Fsrc%3Dembed%5C%22%20data-mce-fragment%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Rainwater%20-%20Bangalore%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22659%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20issue%20lies%20in%20the%20structure%20of%20lake%20management%E2%80%93multiple%20institutes%20oversee%20operations%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20lack%20of%20coordination%20and%20planning%20for%20addressing%20concerns%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Palur.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Bangalore%20Development%20Authority%20handles%20lake%20rejuvenation%20and%20transfers%20maintenance%20responsibilities%20to%20the%20BBMP.%20Although%20funds%20are%20available%2C%20transparency%20regarding%20their%20usage%20is%20lacking%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20remarked.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20resources%20might%20be%20allocated%20for%20beautification%2C%20which%20may%20not%20effectively%20address%20underlying%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20Rashmi%20Kulranjan%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20WELL%20Labs%20and%20a%20co-author%20of%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20researchers%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20regular%20desilting%20of%20lakes%2C%20to%20maintain%20storage%20capacity%2C%20lacks%20oversight%20and%20authority.%20It%20occurs%20sporadically%20for%20select%20lakes%2C%20without%20a%20systematic%20monitoring%20or%20decision-making%20process.%20For%20instance%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbengaluru.urbanwaters.in%2Fcase-study-lake-rejuvenated-for-people-nature-319%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJakkur%20Lake%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0underwent%20desilting%20between%202009%20and%202011%2C%20a%20process%20that%20lasted%20several%20months.%20In%20contrast%2C%20desilting%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbangaloremirror.indiatimes.com%2Fbangalore%2Fcivic%2Flake-finally-sans-silt%2Farticleshow%2F100287541.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBellandur%20Lake%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20been%20going%20on%20for%20over%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3EHigh%20rate%20of%20non-revenue%20water%20(NRW)%20losses%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBengaluru%E2%80%99s%20water%20supply%20network%20consists%20of%206%2C000%20km%20of%20pipelines%2C%2060%20booster%20pumps%2C%2084%20ground-level%20reservoirs%20and%20over%2052%20overhead%20tanks.%20It%20pumps%20about%201%2C520%20MLD%20water%2C%20of%20which%20about%20448%20(nearly%2030%25)%20is%20%E2%80%9Clost%E2%80%9D.%20This%20includes%20unaccounted-for%20losses%20of%20water%20through%20pipeline%20leakages%20and%20unauthorised%20connections.%20The%20report%20estimates%20%E2%80%9Creal%20losses%E2%80%9D%2C%20i.e.%20losses%20caused%20by%20poor%20infrastructure%2C%20to%20be%20about%20331%20MLD.%20The%20rest%20is%20considered%20%E2%80%9Capparent%20losses%E2%80%9D%2C%20i.e.%20losses%20caused%20by%20unauthorised%20connections%2C%20dysfunctional%20water%20metering%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%202016%2C%20Bengaluru%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2Fbengaluru-wastes-nearly-50-water-supply-from-cauvery-53879%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehad%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20second%20highest%20rate%20of%20non-revenue%20water%20(NRW)%20among%20Indian%20cities%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiaspend.com%2Fbengaluru-wastes-nearly-50-water-supply-from-cauvery-53879%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20September%20that%20year.%20%E2%80%9CReducing%20losses%20cannot%20occur%20immediately%3B%20it%20requires%20the%20overhaul%20of%20the%20entire%20infrastructure.%20The%20NRW%20rate%20decreased%20from%2050%25%20in%202017%20to%20the%20current%20estimated%2030%25%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kulranjan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20draggable%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20contenteditable%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20data-height-original%3D%5C%22871%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fe.infogram.com%2Fd94add55-b830-4f65-98a7-286e9b33a14d%3Fsrc%3Dembed%5C%22%20data-mce-fragment%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Water%20Distribution%20In%20Bangalore%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22871%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20such%20losses%20serve%20as%20a%20primary%20source%20of%20groundwater%20recharge.%20Introducing%20NRW%20reduction%20schemes%20could%20actually%20lead%20to%20a%20decline%20in%20groundwater%20recharge.%20To%20counterbalance%20this%2C%20the%20city%20must%20prioritise%20investments%20in%20rainwater%20harvesting.%20This%20option%20proves%20more%20viable%E2%80%93both%20in%20terms%20of%20economics%20and%20prudent%20energy%20use%E2%80%93compared%20to%20importing%20additional%20surface%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAlthough%20rainwater%20harvesting%20is%20mandatory%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20buildings%20harvest%20rainwater%20for%20recharge%20rather%20than%20direct%20use.%20A%20small%20but%20growing%20number%20of%20residents%20and%20institutions%20have%20invested%20in%20sub-surface%20or%20on-surface%20storage%20to%20enable%20them%20to%20use%20a%20substantial%20amount%20of%20rainwater%20for%20direct%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3EOnly%2030%25%20of%20wastewater%20is%20reused%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOf%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20net%20wastewater%2C%2024%25%20remains%20untreated.%20Among%20treated%20wastewater%2C%2063%25%20undergo%20centralised%20treatment%2C%20and%2013%25%20through%20decentralised%20plants.%20But%20only%2030%25%20of%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20total%20wastewater%20is%20reused.%20There%20is%20a%20substantial%20potential%20to%20expand%20the%20treatment%20infrastructure.%20This%20could%20support%20various%20activities%2C%20including%20construction%20and%20enhancing%20public%20spaces%2C%20and%20relieving%20pressure%20on%20freshwater%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20vast%20amount%20of%20wastewater%20is%20an%20untapped%20resource%2C%20capable%20of%20reducing%20freshwater%20consumption%20and%20enhancing%20water%20resilience%20during%20periods%20of%20low%20rainfall%2C%20the%20report%20points%20out.%20Sectors%20like%20watering%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20green%20spaces%2C%20the%20construction%20industry%2C%20and%20aquifer%20recharge%20can%20substitute%20freshwater%20with%20treated%20wastewater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20draggable%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20contenteditable%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20data-height-original%3D%5C%22775%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fe.infogram.com%2Fdca9395f-bcf7-490c-8b93-b1da55669edb%3Fsrc%3Dembed%5C%22%20data-mce-fragment%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Waste%20Water%20Treatment%20In%20Bangalore%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22775%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CUsing%20treated%20water%20instead%20of%20fresh%20water%20for%20non-essential%20activities%20is%20a%20positive%20measure%2C%20which%20should%20be%20sustained%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Palur.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20is%20also%20advocating%20for%20the%20utilisation%20of%20the%20BWSSB%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F49.50.101.199%2Fstp%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eportal%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20request%20tertiary%20water%20plants%2C%20facilitating%20water%20procurement%20for%20needy%20areas%20of%20the%20city.%20Until%20recently%2C%20this%20resource%20had%20been%20underutilised.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMost%20city%20treatment%20facilities%20perform%20only%20secondary%20treatment%2C%20the%20report%20says.%20This%20is%20not%20sufficient%20to%20significantly%20reduce%20the%20nutrient%20concentration%20in%20wastewater%2C%20which%20contributes%20to%20lake%20eutrophication%20(the%20process%20in%20which%20a%20water%20body%20becomes%20overly%20enriched%20with%20nutrients%2C%20leading%20to%20plentiful%20growth%20of%20plant%20life).%20Algal%20blooms%20in%20city%20lakes%20are%20evidence%20of%20this%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20crisis%2C%20the%20Karnataka%20government%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkarnataka%2Fbengaluru%2Fbengaluru-water-crisis-government-caps-water-tanker-prices-in-the-city-2926362%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eannounced%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0plans%20to%20assume%20control%20of%20water%20tankers%20and%20cap%20prices.%20However%2C%20Palur%20suggests%20that%20this%20approach%20may%20not%20be%20sustainable.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20escalating%20prices%20stem%20from%20suppliers%20having%20to%20fetch%20water%20from%20increasingly%20distant%20locations.%20Unless%20the%20state%20absorbs%20these%20additional%20costs%2C%20supplying%20at%20capped%20rates%20would%20be%20unsustainable%20for%20tanker%20operators.%E2%80%9D%20Furthermore%2C%20Palur%20notes%20that%20the%20only%20long-term%20solution%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aninews.in%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fgeneral-news%2Fvrishabhavati-project-will-resolve-bengalurus-water-problems-karnataka-cm-siddaramaiah20240304201055%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eannounced%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20government%2C%20the%20Vrishabhavati%20lift%20irrigation%20project%2C%20lacks%20clarity%20regarding%20its%20potential%20benefits%20for%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndiaSpend%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0has%20reached%20out%20to%20BBMP%20and%20BWSSB%20to%20inquir