en%20rice%20grains%20meant%20%3Cem%3EDanda%20Kattna%3C%2Fem%3E%20pooja%20for%20auspicious%20activities%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20peculiar%20thing%20about%20Oraon%20paintings%20is%20that%20mud%20forms%20the%20main%20base%20due%20to%20the%20availability%20of%20various%20types%20of%20soils.%20The%20community%20creates%20different%20shades%20of%20black%2C%20brown%20and%20red%20from%20the%20soil.%20Green%20and%20white%20colours%20are%20made%20from%20leaves%20and%20rice%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumanti%20says%20she%20adds%20glue%20to%20the%20colours%20so%20that%20it%20sticks%20to%20the%20canvas.%20To%20date%2C%20she%20and%20the%20people%20from%20her%20village%20have%20not%20used%20acrylic%20or%20synthetic%20colours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20mentions%20two%20reasons%20for%20this%2C%20%E2%80%9CFirstly%2C%20accessibility%20and%20cost%20came%20in%20the%20way%2C%20and%20secondly%2C%20natural%20colours%20are%20a%20very%20important%20part%20of%20our%20identity.%20Our%20ancestors%20were%20confined%20to%20villages%2C%20so%20they%20made%20natural%20colours%20on%20their%20own%20and%20took%20pride%20in%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EColours%20that%20come%20from%20the%20soil%20are%20seen%20as%20sacred%2C%20she%20informs.%20The%20elders%20of%20the%20house%20perform%20a%20brief%20ritual%2C%20praying%20for%20an%20obstacle-free%20search%20for%20the%20right%20soil.%20While%20red%20and%20brown%20soils%20were%20readily%20accessible%2C%20finding%20black%20ones%20was%20challenging%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20ancestors%20would%20have%20to%20dig%20in%20forests%20to%20find%20the%20black%20soil.%20The%20rarity%20factor%20makes%20the%20soil%20so%20important%20in%20our%20culture.%20Besides%2C%20these%20three%20colours%20are%20used%20in%20all%20our%20%3Cem%3Epujas%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20date.%20According%20to%20a%20legend%2C%20Mahadev%20and%20Parvati%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20told%20our%20ancestors%20to%20use%20these%20colours%2C%E2%